						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of a perpetual lamp to the Perumānaḍigaḷ at Gōvindapāḍi in Valla-nāḍu a division of Dāmarkōṭṭam in Toṇḍai-nāḍu, by queen Amanimādēviyār on behalf of her elder sister Kambaṉ Guṇakānti. The donor is also called Rāśingam and referred to as a <hi rend="italic">Manavāsi</hi> (native) of Poḻiyūr in Poḻiyūrnāḍu a division of Pāṇḍi-nāḍu. </p>						

						</summary>
